    "recap_headline": "Rice University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "Houston-\nHouston jumped on Rice early and rolled to a 13-1 win in the opening game of the 2026 Silver Glove Series at Schroeder Park on Tuesday night.\nHow it Happened:\nThe Cougars took an early lead with a two-run homer in the bottom of the first and went on to add runs in the third, fourth, and fifth before ending the game in the eighth with five. \u00a0\u00a0In the top of the eighth, the Owls cashed in on their best scoring chance.\nKutter-Gage Webb\nwalked, then moved to third on\nMason Ashlock's\nblistering double down the left field line. Landis Davilla then brought Webb in with a groundout to break the shutout.\nNext Up:\nRice heads west this weekend for a four-game weekend set of games featuring two against both Saint Mary's and Grand Canyon.\u00a0 The action opens with a doubleheader on Friday, facing Saint Mary's at 3 p.m. (central) and Grand Canyon at 8 p.m.\nNotes\nRice fell to 9-8 on the season, 3-5 on the road, and 0-3 on Tuesdays.\nThe Owls run in the eighth inning allowed them to avoid the first shutout in the Silver Glove Series since a 1-0 Cougar win in 2018.\nColin Robson\nled off the game with an infield single, and is hitting .363 this season leading off a game.\nAshlock has hit in five of his last six (.313, 5x16).\nReliever\nCarson Kuhn\nstruck out three in the seventh and has struck out seven this season in three innings.\n."
